DominanceSetupDetailed
data.value:
This command is used to set up the entire dominance module in one go. You can set up each individual role using the website as well if you do not want to use this wizard.

After executing the command in DIscord, you will be presented with a setup message from the bot which tells you what to do on each step. First, you set which role you want to use as the dominance discount role, and then you assign a role to each flight.

There are multiple ways to provide the roles to the bot:

  • Using a ping, eg. @role
  • Using the role's ID (How do I get an ID?)
  • Simply type in the role's name without the @

After the setup is complete, users will have to sign up to receive the dominance role using the command dom optin.

data.name: DominanceUpdateDetailed
data.value:
Using this command starts a manual update of the dominance status. The bot will find what flight is dominating and update the roles accordingly.

You should only use this command if:

  • If anyone's changed flight roles and you'd like them to update. Currently, the dominance role is not automatically applied/removed when people change the assigned flight roles.
  • If, for some reason, the bot doesn't update roles after dominance rolls over. This might happen due to circumstances out of our control, but you probably want to let us know on Github anyway since it might be a bug.

data.name: SkinTesterPreviewDetailed
data.value:
Allows you to preview your requested skin on a dragon of your choice. You can supply:

  • an existing dragon ID
  • a scry image URL
  • a dressing room image URL

You can swap the gender of your dragon by adding -s at the end of your command. This only works when previewing on an existing dragon using it's ID.
Morphologies also work, both from the scrying workshop and the dressing room. By default all images shown don't include apparel (if available), if you want a preview with the skin and apparel on you add -apparel at the end of your command.
